Hello Raffaella,

Please find my responses and details provided below in green for easy refer=
ence.

Attached are the documents which have been produced in relation to your cla=
im to date.

In reading both of your recent emails I can identify the areas of your clai=
m that you have requested further clarification on. I have reasoned that yo=
ur enquiries are centered around 4 general areas of the claim response. As =
follows:

  1.  Forensic testing of resulting damages and testing methodology with re=
spect to clearances.
  2.  Structural assessment of resulting damages and testing methodology wi=
th respect to clearances.
  3.  Consenting and Compliance regarding the repairs required.
  4.  Policy Response [ The specific coverage and benefits which can be app=
lied to your claim by your insurer ]
  5.  Privacy requests.

The only instrument available to Tower Insurance is to appoint professional=
 service providers to attend, discuss, assess, test and report on the areas=
 and the aspects of the property which you have suggested where they may be=
 resulting damage.

When referring to the 5 different fields above; the responses can be provid=
ed by the following 5 entities:

1&2       - Tower Insurance will request that a CPEng and a Forensic Scient=
ist are to attend, discuss, assess, test and report on the areas and the as=
pects of the property which you have requested or suggested where they may =
be resulting damage.

3            - ASURNZ to provide consenting and compliance advice.

4            - For Policy Response =E2=80=93 Kelly Mason & Bryan Strong wou=
ld provide response and discussion on this aspect of your claim.

5            - For your privacy request our claims department is currently =
compiling the requested documents.

In summary the proposed site meeting/assessment attendees to assess and pro=
vide adequate responses to your enquires would be:
Bryan Strong =E2=80=93 Senior Manager Property Assessing
Grant Metson =E2=80=93 Regional Assessing Manager
Kelly Mason =E2=80=93 Technical Claim Resolution Specialist
Stephen Walker =E2=80=93 Technical Building Consultant. ASURNZ.
Warwick Banks =E2=80=93 Associate Structural Engineer. CPEng
Alexandra Dalzell =E2=80=93 Forensic Scientist

Further details for CPEng, Forensic Scientist and Technical Consultant prov=
ided below at the bottom of my response.

Agenda for meeting:

  1.  Greeting and Introductions.
  2.  Discuss and assess potential chemical contamination from the pool che=
micals which were present in the location of the fire. Discuss forward test=
ing and clearance methodology.
  3.  Discuss and assess potential wall cavity smoke contamination. Provide=
 written methodology and scope of testing to determine the degree of testin=
g, and to discuss proposed remediation methods where contamination is found=
 to be present.
  4.  CPEng Engineer to observe and assess structural integrity of the prop=
erty in respect of claim related damages from the fire and provide a descri=
ption of adequate repair methodology.
  5.  Discuss the application of schedule 1 of the building act to establis=
h the requirement, or not, of a building consent.
  6.  Tower Representatives can discuss any general policy response enquiri=
es.
  7.  Agree and document next steps in claim progression.
Thank you for considering my response. The above proposal is the best that =
I can provide to respond to your enquiries and to enable the progression of=
 your claim.
The above does not have to be the full and final response =E2=80=93 however=
 I do sincerely believe that if the above specialist professionals can atte=
nd, listen, discuss, and provide well qualified responses =E2=80=93 then we=
 can move forward to the next phase of determining the final scope to enabl=
e repairs to begin.
Further detail of professional specialists directly below.
I respectfully ask you to consider the above and reply to me in due course =
if you are happy to proceed with the above.

Sincere Regards.
Grant.

