<p>Kia ora Grant,&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>Thanks for your email and for proposing to bring stakeholders together. =
As you=E2=80=99ve said, you =E2=80=9C will gather the supporting informatio=
n=E2=80=A6 and provide that=E2=80=A6&nbsp;well ahead&nbsp;of [any] site mee=
ting,=E2=80=9D and you=E2=80=99ll send an agenda based on my email.&nbsp;<o=
:p></o:p></p>
<p>Could you please first send your&nbsp;written responses&nbsp;to my quest=
ions and the&nbsp;supporting documents&nbsp;(reports, scope, raw notes/phot=
o logs from prior attendances, and the&nbsp;test-led plan&nbsp;with methods=
, thresholds, labs and pass/fail criteria)? Once I have those,
 I can identify the appropriate experts to attend.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p>Given I rely on third-party availability, please plan on&nbsp;1=E2=80=93=
2 weeks=E2=80=99 notice&nbsp;after I receive your written responses and the=
 agenda. I=E2=80=99m very happy to meet then.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p>To avoid further email back-and-forth, please also include:<o:p></o:p></=
p>
<p><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"color:#0070C0;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-=
margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l10 level1 lfo14">
<span style=3D"color:windowtext">AC2213/Council path&nbsp;(consent or writt=
en exemption) and confirmation of&nbsp;CPEng&nbsp;engagement.
</span>The repairs qualify to be completed under schedule 1 as per extract =
following which is taken from the ASURNZ response provided further below. T=
here is no requirement to provide CPEng engagement. However Tower is prepar=
ed &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.25in"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" sty=
le=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast=
-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"margin-left:.25in"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" sty=
le=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#0070=
C0;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Regarding the provisions of s.112 of the Bui=
lding Act 2004, these do not apply to the repair of
 this dwelling as none of the required building work requires a building co=
nsent.&nbsp; Similarly, the practice note from Auckland Council does not ap=
ply, and in any case is not a regulatory or legislative requirement.&nbsp; =
Note that the defining legislation is the
 Building Act 2004 (the Act).&nbsp; The Act overrides any policy of a build=
ing consent authority.&nbsp; The provisions of the Act make clear that a bu=
ilding consent is not required for the proposed repairs to this dwelling.<o=
:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-=
alt:auto;mso-list:l10 level1 lfo14">
Hold-points&nbsp;and clearances (roof/eaves intrusives, cavities, corrosion=
/pH-chloride, IAQ, whole-installation electrical to AS/NZS 3000, HVAC/gas h=
ygiene);<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto"><u><span style=3D"color:#0070C0">Chemical Contamination Testing<o:=
p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto"><span style=3D"color:#0070C0">Hold points can be established for s=
wab testing for the potential chemical contamination that you have advised =
us of after we have completed base tests.
 To assist in establishing this we must first obtain a schedule of the chem=
icals which were present during the fire, and have it confirmed where they =
were located so appropriate testing can be undertaken. We would appoint a F=
orensic Scientist to undertake testing
 of the current environment and then report their findings to all parties t=
o consider. We can not define hold-points until we understand the extent of=
 the chemical contamination and where it exists.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto"><u><span style=3D"color:#0070C0">Roof &amp; Eaves<o:p></o:p></span=
></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto"><span style=3D"color:#0070C0">There is no need for invasive assess=
ment on these components as they are readily accessible and visible both ex=
ternally and internally.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto"><u><span style=3D"color:#0070C0">Cavities
<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-a=
lt:auto"><span style=3D"color:#0070C0">We have completed invasive cavity in=
spection with your knowledge to determine the condition of the external wal=
l cavities. We can review these during
 the site meeting. &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"color:#0070C0;mso-list:l2 level1 lf=
o15"><span style=3D"color:windowtext">Any directions provided to ASURNZ.
</span>These will be sent you under the privacy request which claims is pro=
cessing now. &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></li></ul>
<p>Once received I=E2=80=99ll revert with attendee names and propose meetin=
g dates within the 1=E2=80=932 week window.<o:p></o:p></p>
