<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white">Hi Grant, I have read through the concerns rais=
ed by your customer in the email below. I think it would be useful for us t=
o clarify the involvement of ASURNZ, our
 independence to Tower Insurance, our experience, and our approach to deter=
mining<o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Hi Grant,<o=
:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">I have read=
 through the concerns raised by your customer in the email below.&nbsp; I t=
hink it would be useful for us to clarify the involvement
 of ASURNZ, our independence to Tower Insurance, our experience, and our ap=
proach to determining remediation required for damage caused by fire, heat,=
 chemicals, and smoke resulting from fire related events.<o:p></o:p></span>=
</p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;fo=
nt-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Fairness=
 and participation<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">ASURNZ oper=
ates as third-party provider specialising in damage assessment and remediat=
ion, building product and building system compliance,
 and legislative and regulatory requirements for building related matters.&=
nbsp; In these matters we also provide expert witness services to the Court=
s.&nbsp; Our customers include private building owners (residential, commer=
cial, and industrial), insurers, building
 consent authorities (including Auckland Council), and building product man=
ufacturers. As such we provide a service that is independent and impartial =
of Tower Insurance.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Details fro=
m our site inspection, including relevant photo schedules are provided in o=
ur reporting, however we understand that homeowners
 will often have property specific questions. We are happy to meet with you=
r customer to go over our findings, and to listen to and consider their con=
cerns.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Fire chemis=
try &amp; severity<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">ASURNZ has =
extensive experience in the assessment and remediation of fire/smoke damage=
d buildings.&nbsp; In all building fires there is risk
 that materials affected by fire can contribute to or cause corrosion from =
airborne means (transfer via smoke and heat).&nbsp; However, corrosion and =
the potential for corrosion of building components is readily assessable fr=
om visible inspection and reasonable
 testing.&nbsp; For example, corrosion on mild steel or galvanised steel co=
mponents and aluminium components (painted or unpainted) will manifest on e=
xposed surfaces of those materials and are immediately apparent on visual i=
nspection.&nbsp; If no significant corrosion
 is present on surfaces directly exposed to heat and smoke, as was the situ=
ation observed in your customers dwelling, enclosed surfaces such as within=
 wall or ceiling cavities will be less affected and therefore will not suff=
er corrosion from fire related fumes.
 &nbsp;In all situations for remediation we consider the following steps in=
 order: cleaning; encapsulation (where cleaning alone is insufficient and t=
he product is not damaged or will not be damaged by cleaning); and replacem=
ent (where neither cleaning nor encapsulation
 will provide effective remediation).&nbsp; These steps also follow the sam=
e principles set out in the Institute of Inspection Cleaning, Restoration, =
and Certification (IICRC) codes of practice.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">However, as=
 your customer has provided new information regarding the possible presence=
 of pool chemicals, we suggest that we engage the
 services of Alexandra Dalzell from Forensic Specialists to undertake testi=
ng for the presence of residual chemicals on selected surfaces throughout t=
he dwelling.&nbsp; The outcomes of such testing will then be used to furthe=
r inform the remediation strategy and
 include, where appropriate, clearance testing post-repair.<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Regarding s=
tructural matters, as this is a timber framed residential building and the =
structure can be addressed using the NZ Standard
 for timber framed buildings not requiring specific engineering design (NZS=
 3604:2011) there is no need for the involvement of a CPEng structural engi=
neer.&nbsp; Further, as one of the authors of NZS 3604 and current chair of=
 that standards development committee
 I provide ASURNZ with specialist timber and timber framing knowledge that =
few engineers have, including regarding the durability of timber and regula=
tory requirements that relate to the repair of existing buildings.&nbsp; Al=
so, the structural damage to timber members
 is readily apparent and relatively localised.&nbsp; In this regard I do no=
t believe there is any benefit to be gained by engaging a CPEng structural =
engineer.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Regarding t=
he provisions of s.112 of the Building Act 2004, these do not apply to the =
repair of this dwelling as none of the required
 building work requires a building consent.&nbsp; Similarly, the practice n=
ote from Auckland Council does not apply, and in any case is not a regulato=
ry or legislative requirement.&nbsp; Note that the defining legislation is =
the Building Act 2004 (the Act).&nbsp; The Act
 overrides any policy of a building consent authority.&nbsp; The provisions=
 of the Act make clear that a building consent is not required for the prop=
osed repairs to this dwelling.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US">Regarding s=
pecific scope queries, I think is best to address these on site in the firs=
t instance.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"><o:p>&nbsp;=
</o:p></span></p>
