o share the results you are relying on for: (i) char/heat checks of boards =
and joists; (ii) moisture readings and decay risk;
 (iii) removal and inspection of representative hangers, bolts and ledger f=
ixings for corrosion/galvanising loss; (iv) ledger-to-wall verification, in=
cluding flashing/weep details; (v) chloride/pH screening at the perimeter a=
nd fixings; and (vi) confirmation
 that the balustrade/handrail meets current requirements. If any results do=
 not meet the engineer=E2=80=99s acceptance criteria, then those components=
