<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:1.0pt;color:white">Hi Grant=
, Thank you for your recent email and for the summary of our meeting. I app=
reciate your efforts to move the claim forward. There are a few important m=
atters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensure
 the process remains safe, fair, and aligned with</span><span style=3D"font=
-size:10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Hi Grant,<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Thank you for your recent email and for the summary of our meeting. I =
appreciate your efforts to move the claim forward.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">There are a few important matters I=E2=80=99d like to clarify to ensur=
e the process remains safe, fair, and aligned with Tower=E2=80=99s responsi=
bilities under the policy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">First, regarding the items I took with me from the property =E2=80=94 =
including my electric vehicle (EV), laptops, tablets, and mobile phones =E2=
=80=94 these were all exposed to heat, smoke, and corrosive
 chemicals (including nearby spa products that intensified the fire). I rem=
ain concerned about internal damage, particularly to lithium batteries, and=
 the potential for delayed failure or fire.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">It is not appropriate or reasonable for Tower to shift the responsibil=
ity for assessing or managing the risk of these items to me. Ensuring they =
are safe for continued use is a critical safety
 issue =E2=80=94 not just a claims matter. Tower must take responsibility f=
or confirming whether these items are safe, and whether they require restor=
ation or replacement.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Second, I would appreciate clarification of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s sc=
ope. Is their role limited to cataloguing and removing contents, or will th=
ey also be undertaking removal of fire- or smoke-damaged
 linings (such as jib and other non-structural internal components)? This d=
etail is important for understanding when and how a proper structural asses=
sment of the property will take place.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Lastly, I would like to request a clear and updated plan for the progr=
ession of the house claim. Could you please provide:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l3 level1 lfo12"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif">A current stat=
us update on the structural assessment and any scoping completed to date;</=
span><span style=3D"font-size:10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"M=
soNormal" style=3D"mso-list:l3 level1 lfo12"><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt=
;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif">A proposed timeline for the =
next phases: removal, scoping, approvals, tendering, and repair;</span><spa=
n style=3D"font-size:10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoNormal"=
 style=3D"mso-list:l3 level1 lfo12"><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-fam=
ily:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif">Confirmation of the parties responsib=
le for each stage and how updates will be communicated.</span><span style=
=3D"font-size:10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></li></ol>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">I look forward to your response addressing the points above.<o:p></o:p=
></span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-se=
rif">Kind regards,<br>
Rafaella<o:p></o:p></span></p>
